# Voxel Sandbox (C++ / OpenGL) 🚧

This repository contains a minimal starter for a voxel sandbox using C++ and OpenGL.

Features:
- Procedural terrain (simple value noise heightmap)
- Chunking (small grid of chunks)
- Mesh generation with face culling
- Basic renderer and shaders

Build (requirements):
- CMake >= 3.16
- A C++17 compiler
- Internet access (CMake FetchContent pulls GLFW and glad)

Quick build:

```bash
cmake -S . -B build
cmake --build build -j
./build/voxel_sandbox
```

Next steps implemented:
- Camera and input (WASD + mouse) ✅
- DDA raycast + block placement/mining ✅
- Greedy meshing and threaded chunk generation ✅

Controls:
- WASD to move, Space / Left Shift to move up/down
- Mouse to look around (cursor locked)
- Left click: mine (remove block)
- Right click: place block adjacent to hit face

Notes:
- Mesh generation runs on background threads; CPU-meshes are uploaded to GPU on the main thread to avoid GL context issues.
- Greedy meshing reduces triangle count compared to naive faces-per-voxel.
